# Firebase / FCM.
# IMPORTANT: google-services.json is the Android *client* build config, NOT a
# server secret — its API key is restricted by package name + app-signing SHA,
# so committing it is safe and expected. The APK build (local or CI) must have
# it on disk at build time; without it Firebase never initialises and killed-app
# push notifications never arrive. It is therefore intentionally NOT ignored.
# (Prefer not to commit it? Set GOOGLE_SERVICES_JSON as a build env var and
# scripts/write-google-services.mjs will write the file at build time.)
# Genuine secrets stay ignored below — inject via env/secrets, never commit:
GoogleService-Info.plist
firebase-service-account*.json
serviceAccountKey*.json
